June 4 (Reuters) -  U.S. stocks were largely flat on Wednesday as mixed reads on the economy gave the market little direction and traders were reluctant to buy with indexes near record levels. The Dow Jones industrial average <.DJI> was up 0.04 percent at 16,728.41 and the S&P 500 <.SPX> was up 0.15 percent at 1,927.1. [.N]

** LSB FINANCIAL CORP <LSBI.O>, $40.05, +41.52 pct Old National Bancorp said it would acquire LSB Financial, which owns the Lafayette Savings Bank, for about $66.7 million. LSB Financial shareholders will receive 2.269 shares of Old National common stock and $10.63 in cash, or about $41.67, per share held. [ID:nGNXVASUKa]  ** NQ MOBILE INC <NQ.N>, $10.029, +31.44 pct The Chinese mobile security software maker said a special committee had found no evidence of fraud, as alleged by short-seller Muddy Waters Research Group. [ID:nL3N0OL2VS]   ** TF FINANCIAL CORP <THRD.O>, $41.77, +31.19 pct Bank holding company National Penn Bancshares Inc <NPBC.O> said it would acquire TF Financial for $138 million. TF Financial shareholders may elect to receive $42 in cash, or 4.22 shares of National Penn stock, for each share held.  TF Financial owns 3rd Fed Bank, an FDIC-insured savings bank. [ID:nBw8X4w5ka]** VANDA PHARMACEUTICALS INC <VNDA.O>, $12.364, +23.39 pct The drugmaker said European regulators accepted for evaluation a marketing application for its sleep disorder drug, Hetlioz. [ID:nPn4d4kXP] Hetlioz was approved in the United States in January to treat Non-24-Hour Sleep-Wake disorder.   ** DRAGONWAVE INC <DRWI.O>, $1.451, +18.74 pct The wireless networking equipment maker <DWI.TO> raised its first-quarter revenue growth forecast to 60 percent from 50 percent. [ID:nCCN2qCv6C]  ** PROTECTIVE LIFE CORP <PL.N>, $69.31, +18.03 pct Japan's Dai-ichi Life Insurance Co <8750.T> has agreed to buy U.S. peer Protective Life for $5.7 billion, the largest acquisition by a Japanese insurer, displaying its determination to grow overseas to counter weak prospects at home. [ID:nL3N0OL0Z0]   ** YINGLI GREEN ENERGY HOLD CO LTD <YGE.N>, $2.84, -3.73 pct ** RENESOLA LTD <SOL.N>, $2.24, -3.03 pct ** HANWHA SOLARONE CO LTD <HSOL.O>, $2.22, -3.06 pct ** TRINA SOLAR LTD <TSL.N>, $12.73, -1.85 pct ** JINKOSOLAR HOLDING CO LTD <JKS.N>, $25.87, -4.26 pct ** CHINA SUNERGY CO LTD <CSUN.O>, $3.09, +3.00